FBIS3-5059 "dreas042_c_94028" FBIS-EAS-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 North Korea Minister of Mining Industry Replaced 2 Mar SK0303114294 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1100 GMT 3 Mar 94 SK0303114294 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1100 GMT 3 Mar 94 Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [Text] A decree of the DPRK Central People's Committee [CPC] on dismissal and appointment of a minister of the DPRK State Administration Council: The DPRK CPC decides as follows: Comrade Kim Pil-hwan has been relieved from his post of minister of mining industry of the State Administration Council and Comrade Kim Pyong-kil has been appointed as minister of mining industry of the State Administration Council. DPRK President Kim Il-song 2 March 1994, Pyongyang
